                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14100075" author="apachespark" created="Sun, 17 Aug 2014 19:31:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;User &apos;sarutak&apos; has created a pull request for this issue:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/2001&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/2001&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14107488" author="vanzin" created="Fri, 22 Aug 2014 21:08:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think that if we want to add this, it would be better to do so for all modes, not just yarn-client. Basically have SparkContext itself register a shutdown hook to shut itself down, and publish the priority of the hook so that apps / backends can register hooks that run before it (see Hadoop&apos;s ShutdownHookManager for the priority thing - &lt;a href=&quot;http://goo.gl/BQ1bjk&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://goo.gl/BQ1bjk&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That way the code in the yarn-cluster backend can be removed too.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14117036" author="sarutak" created="Mon, 1 Sep 2014 05:20:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It sound good idea that SparkContext register shutdown-hook itself.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14512048" author="apachespark" created="Fri, 24 Apr 2015 23:50:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;User &apos;vanzin&apos; has created a pull request for this issue:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/5696&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/5696&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
